"{\"uid\": \"ca.news.yahoo.com-olympics-wada-confirms-23-chinese-092918065.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Manage your account (Reuters) -The World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) confirmed reports on Saturday that 23 Chinese swimmers tested positive for a banned drug before the 2020 Tokyo Olympics but it accepted the country's findings that this was due to substance contamination.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30, \"end\": 37, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.322815854469978e-13, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 44, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 44, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 114, \"end\": 121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9608779898717694, \"rank\": 0.04068927600129912, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your account\", \"from\": 7, \"to\": 19}, {\"ngram\": \"(Reuters\", \"from\": 20, \"to\": 28}, {\"ngram\": \"reports\", \"from\": 77, \"to\": 84}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 88, \"to\": 96}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned drug\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 155}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 163, \"to\": 186}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's findings\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 225}, {\"ngram\": \"due to substance contamination\", \"from\": 240, \"to\": 270}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Multiple media reports said the swimmers tested positive for trimetazidine (TMZ), which is found in heart medication, months before the COVID-delayed Games began in the Japanese capital in July 2021.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.958507587988877, \"rank\": 0.02949458635134648, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Multiple media reports\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 304}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"trimetazidine\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 356}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 361}, {\"ngram\": \"heart medication\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"the COVID-delayed Games\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 437}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 475}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CHINADA, China's anti-doping agency, called the reports \\\"misleading\\\" and said the positive results had been inadvertent.\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9941859226821699, \"rank\": 0.005847245834307529, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 490}, {\"ngram\": \"the reports\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 538}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive results\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CHINADA said the swimmers had tested positive for \\\"extremely low concentration\\\" of TMZ after inadvertently being exposed to the substance through contamination and should not be held responsible for the positive results, according to a statement reported by China's state news agency Xinhua on Sunday.\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 863, \"end\": 868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9941859226821699, \"rank\": 0.005847245834307529, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.726299914674688e-34, \"text\": \"Xinhua\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 630}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"extremely low concentration\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 691}, {\"ngram\": \"the substance\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 742}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive results\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 905}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Chinese anti-doping agency said it had investigated the matter \\\"from various respects\\\" and kept WADA and World Aquatics informed.\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9608779898717694, \"rank\": 0.04068927600129912, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the matter\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 974}, {\"ngram\": \"various respects\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1031}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"WADA agreed with our conclusion after thorough review,\\\" CHINADA said.\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1112, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"our conclusion\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"thorough review\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Chinese Swimming Association did not respond to an email from Reuters seeking comment.\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Swimming_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chinese Swimming Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Swimming_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Swimming_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1180, \"end\": 1187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.322815854469978e-13, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an email\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"comment\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA said it was notified in June 2021 of CHINADA's decision to accept that the swimmers returned adverse analytical findings, or AAFs, after inadvertently being exposed to the drug through contamination.\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1410, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1210}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA's decision\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"adverse analytical findings\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1331}, {\"ngram\": \"AAFs\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"the drug\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1387}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1409}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The global anti-doping body, which has the authority to appeal the rulings of national doping agencies, said it reviewed the decision and consulted scientific experts and external legal counsel to test the contamination theory presented by CHINADA.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1660, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The global anti-doping body\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1439}, {\"ngram\": \"the authority\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1464}, {\"ngram\": \"the rulings\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1486}, {\"ngram\": \"national doping agencies\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"scientific experts\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"external legal counsel\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"the contamination theory\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1638}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1659}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"WADA ultimately concluded that it was not in a position to disprove the possibility that contamination was the source of TMZ and it was compatible with the analytical data in the file,\\\" the anti-doping body said in a statement.\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1890, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"a position\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1718}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1746}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1765}, {\"ngram\": \"the source\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"the analytical data\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1834}, {\"ngram\": \"the file\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"the anti-doping body\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"WADA also concluded that ... the athletes would be held to have no fault or negligence.\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1934}, {\"ngram\": \"no fault\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1965}, {\"ngram\": \"negligence\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, and based on the advice of external counsel, WADA considered an appeal was not warranted.\\\"\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2080, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the advice\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2013}, {\"ngram\": \"external counsel\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2039}, {\"ngram\": \"an appeal\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2060}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China's 30-member swimming team won six medals at the Tokyo Games, including three golds.\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2082, \"end\": 2087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9941859226821699, \"rank\": 0.005847245834307529, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"six medals\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2147}, {\"ngram\": \"three golds\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without mitigating circumstances, athletes who fail doping tests are usually subject to bans of two to four years for a first offence and life for a second.\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"circumstances\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2215}, {\"ngram\": \"doping tests\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2237}, {\"ngram\": \"bans\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"two to four years\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2286}, {\"ngram\": \"a first offence\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2306}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2315}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Aquatics, the sport's global body formerly known as FINA, said it was confident the positive tests were handled \\\"diligently and professionally.\\\"\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2389, \"end\": 2393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.46545216302341e-44, \"text\": \"FINA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2345}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's global body\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2370}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With regard to the AAFs ... they were carefully considered by the FINA Doping Control Review Board,\\\" it added.\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2550, \"end\": 2554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.46545216302341e-44, \"text\": \"FINA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"regard\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2495}, {\"ngram\": \"the AAFs\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Materials relating to the source of the AAFs were subject to independent expert scrutiny retained by FINA.\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2697, \"end\": 2701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.46545216302341e-44, \"text\": \"FINA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FINA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Materials\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2605}, {\"ngram\": \"the source\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"the AAFs\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2640}, {\"ngram\": \"independent expert scrutiny\", \"from\": 2657, \"to\": 2684}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"World Aquatics is confident that these AAFs were handled diligently and professionally, and in accordance with applicable anti-doping regulations, including the WADA Code.\\\"\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2877, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2719}, {\"ngram\": \"these AAFs\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"accordance\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2810}, {\"ngram\": \"applicable anti-doping regulations\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2850}, {\"ngram\": \"the WADA Code\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 2875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"POSITIVE TESTS The U.S. Anti-Doping Agency (USADA) criticized WADA and CHINADA for their handling of the matter.\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2924, \"end\": 2929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The U.S. Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2921}, {\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2945}, {\"ngram\": \"CHINADA\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2957}, {\"ngram\": \"their handling\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2976}, {\"ngram\": \"the matter\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 2990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's crushing to see that 23 Chinese swimmers had positive tests for a potent performance-enhancing drug on the eve of the 2021 Olympic Games, as reported by the New York Times,\\\" USADA CEO Travis Tygart said in a statement.\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3024, \"end\": 3031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9608779898717694, \"rank\": 0.04068927600129912, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999998778234914, \"rank\": 1.0833414878669444e-07, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USADA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 3184, \"end\": 3197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"positive tests\", \"from\": 3045, \"to\": 3059}, {\"ngram\": \"a potent performance-enhancing drug\", \"from\": 3064, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"the eve\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3110}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2021 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3136}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's even more devastating to learn the World Anti-Doping Agency and the Chinese Anti-Doping Agency secretly, until now, swept these positives under the carpet by failing to fairly and evenly follow the global rules that apply to everyone else in the world.\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3294, \"end\": 3301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9608779898717694, \"rank\": 0.04068927600129912, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the World Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 3257, \"to\": 3285}, {\"ngram\": \"these positives\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3363}, {\"ngram\": \"the carpet\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3380}, {\"ngram\": \"the global rules\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3436}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3459}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All of those with dirty hands in burying positive tests and suppressing the voices of courageous whistleblowers must be held accountable to the fullest extent of the rules and law.\\\"\", \"from\": 3480, \"to\": 3662, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dirty hands\", \"from\": 3499, \"to\": 3510}, {\"ngram\": \"positive tests\", \"from\": 3522, \"to\": 3536}, {\"ngram\": \"the voices\", \"from\": 3553, \"to\": 3563}, {\"ngram\": \"courageous whistleblowers\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3592}, {\"ngram\": \"the fullest extent\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3639}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3652}, {\"ngram\": \"law\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WADA told Reuters it was considering legal action against USADA and Tygart for accusing it of a cover-up.\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3674, \"end\": 3681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905,